    "body": "So technically, its entirely possible to communicate with multiple nodes in a single app (not sure id call it a Dapp). If you are using nodejs and web3 you could code the 4 RPC urls into a config file and switch between them, setting the `web3.setProvider` function. You can't connect to more than one provider at a time but you could use some kind of Promise.then() daisy chain to make requests to each of them from a single function.\r\n\r\nThat said, I'm not sure why you would want to do that. You only really need one blockchain connected node to interact with the network. And again, this is not a bug/issue with geth so im not sure go-ethereum github is the appropriate forum for Dapp level support.",
